<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The code uses an invariant controlling expression: if (1) { /* ... */ }. MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.3 forbids invariant controlling expressions except for infinite loops or the specific do { ... } while (0) macro pattern that evaluates to false. This instance is neither an infinite loop nor the permitted do-while form, so it violates Rule 14.3. Suggested fixes: remove the if (1) and keep the block, cast the unused variable to void (e.g. (void)res;), or use an approved suppression mechanism (e.g. a compiler pragma) instead of a constant if.
</scenario>

